  <div class="section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">💁‍♀️ Working at nilenso</h2>
    <p class="section-content">
      We are a boutique consulting firm based in Bangalore (though we are fully remote at the moment and our members are
      free to work from any location of their choice), structured as an employee-owned cooperative. Together, we’re
      building an open, inclusive company.
    </p>
    <p class="section-content">
      To us, programming is not just a job. We care deeply about the craft of creation, and the impact we make in the
      world.
    </p>
    <p class="section-content">
      We are tool agnostic, and are currently building software in Clojure as well as Haskell, Elixir, Ruby/Rails,
      Python,
      Go, and Javascript. We incorporated in 2013, have a steady track record of doing deeply technical work. Check out
      our website to see who we’ve worked with, and the <a target="_blank" href="talks.html">talks</a> we’ve given at
      conferences in India and around the world.
    </p>
    <p class="section-content">
      You can find more details about how we do our work, what growth looks like, and other FAQs on our
      <a target="_blank" href="https://vyakaran.nilenso.com/">employee
        handbook</a>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">🗓 What you can expect to learn</h2>
    <p class="section-content">
      You will spend about twelve months learning tools and practices that will enable you to kick-start your career in
      software development. You will be guided throughout the training period, and will also have opportunities to learn
      from the many experienced developers at nilenso. You can expect to learn:
    </p>
    <div class="section-content">
      <ul>
        <li>A new programming language</li>
        <li>Tools like git, that enable modern development processes</li>
        <li>Practices like iterative development, pair programming</li>
        <li>Writing tests, CI/CD</li>
        <li>Working with unix tools</li>
        <li>How to design, develop, and deploy backend applications</li>
        <li>What working on a real project feels like, by shadowing on one</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">📝 What we expect from you</h2>
    <h3>👩‍💻 Programming skills</h3>
    <div class="section-content">
      <ul>
        <li>
          Working knowledge of at least one programming language. Share with us the most significant work you have done.
        </li>
        <li>
          Expect us to ask you about the assumptions you've made, the questions you had etc.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>📚 Ability to learn independently</h3>
    <div class="section-content">
      <ul>
        <li>Track record of having learnt something significant by yourself.</li>
        <li>Ability to dive into details, and have beyond surface level knowledge about the things you have learnt.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3>🧐 Demonstrable interest in writing software</h3>
    <div class="section-content">
      <ul>
        <li>
          Show us your code! We would expect you to be able to walk us through your code, or at least talk about it in
          detail.
        </li>
        <li>
          Tell us about online courses you’ve taken, meetups or conferences you’ve attended, open source contributions
          you’ve made, or an interesting book you’ve read.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

